# Critical Rules

## TypeScript Strict Mode

- No `any` types - use `unknown` if type truly unknown
- No `as any` or `as unknown as <Type>` assertions
- All code must compile without errors
- Prefer `satisfies` over `as` for type narrowing

## Environment Variables

- Never commit `.env` files with secrets
- Use `import.meta.env` for Vite environment variables
- Prefix public variables with `VITE_`
- Validate environment variables at startup

```typescript
const API_URL = import.meta.env.VITE_API_URL
if (!API_URL) throw new Error('VITE_API_URL is required')
```

## React Router Navigation

- Use typed route parameters
- Route params for IDs/primitives only
- Use React Router's `useNavigate` for programmatic navigation
- Define routes centrally in App.tsx or a routes file

```typescript
// Good
navigate('/users/123')
navigate(-1) // go back

// Avoid
window.location.href = '/users/123'
```

## Form Handling

- Use controlled components with proper TypeScript types
- Validate on submit and optionally on blur
- Show clear error messages near the relevant fields
- Disable submit button while submitting

## Performance

- Use React.lazy() for route-based code splitting
- Virtualize long lists (react-window, TanStack Virtual)
- Optimize images (WebP, lazy loading)
- Minimize bundle size with tree shaking

## File Organization

```
src/
├── components/     # Reusable UI components
├── pages/          # Route page components
├── hooks/          # Custom React hooks
├── theme/          # Theme and styling
├── utils/          # Utility functions
├── types/          # TypeScript type definitions
└── services/       # API services
```
